label.value: protein binding involved in cell-cell adhesion

label.value: collagen fibril binding

label.value: protein binding involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any protein binding that is involved in cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: protein complex involved in cell adhesion

definition.value: Any protein complex that is capable of carrying out some part of the process of cell-cell adhesion.

label.value: protein complex involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any protein complex that is capable of carrying out some part of the process of cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: laminin binding involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any laminin protein binding that occurs as part of cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: collagen binding involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any collagen binding that occurs as part of cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: integrin binding involved in cell-matrix adhesion

definition.value: Any integrin binding that occurs as part of the process of cell-matrix adhesion.

label.value: cadherin binding involved in cell-cell adhesion

definition.value: Any cadherin binding that occurs as part of the process of cell-cell adhesion.

label.value: network-forming collagen trimer

definition.value: A collagen trimer that forms networks.

label.value: banded collagen fibril

definition.value: A supramolecular assembly of fibrillar collagen complexes in the form of a long fiber (fibril) with transverse striations (bands).

label.value: complex of collagen trimers

definition.value: A complex of collagen trimers such as a fibril or collagen network.

label.value: collagen network

definition.value: A protein complex that consists of collagen triple helices associated to form a network.

label.value: collagen sheet

definition.value: A protein complex that consists of collagen triple helices associated to form a sheet-like network.

label.value: collagen beaded filament

definition.value: A supramolecular assembly of collagen trimers with a 'beads on a string'-like structure.

label.value: collagen anchoring fibril

definition.value: A specialised collagen fibril that functions as an anchor, binding to other collagen structures.

label.value: peptidyl-proline 4-dioxygenase binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a peptidyl-proline 4-dioxygenase.

label.value: basement membrane collagen trimer

definition.value: Any collagen timer that is part of a basement membrane.

label.value: collagen type VII anchoring fibril

definition.value: An antiparallel dimer of two collagen VII trimers, one end of which is embedded in the lamina densa while the other end attaches to banded collagen fibrils in the dermis.

label.value: CENP-A recruiting complex

definition.value: A protein complex that includes Mis16(Yippee family) and|or Mis18 (WD repeat) subunits that is involved in the deposition of centromere specific (CENP-A containing) nucleosomes at the centromere.

label.value: transmembrane transporter activity involved in import into cell

definition.value: Any transmembrane transporter activity that is involved in importing some substance into a cell.

label.value: chromosomal region

definition.value: Any subdivision of a chromosome along its length.

label.value: skeletal muscle myofibril

definition.value: A myofibril of a skeletal muscle fiber.

label.value: hemidesmosome associated protein complex

definition.value: Any protein complex that is part of or has some part in a hemidesmosome.

label.value: 1-phosphatidylinositol 4-kinase activator activity

definition.value: Increases the activity of 1-phosphatidylinositol 4-kinase.

label.value: Dcp1-Dcp2 complex

definition.value: A protein complex consisting of a Dcp1 regulatory subunit and a Dcp2 catalytic subunit that has mRNA cap binding activity and is involved in decapping of nuclear-transcribed mRNA.

label.value: endocytic adaptor activity

definition.value: The binding activity of a molecule that brings together two or more protein molecules, or a protein and another macromolecule or complex as a key step in receptor mediated endocytosis.

label.value: FYXD domain binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a FXYD domain.

label.value: integral component of the cytoplasmic side of the plasma membrane

definition.value: The component of the plasma membrane consisting of the gene products that penetrate only the cytoplasmic side of the membrane.

label.value: anchored component of the cytoplasmic side of the plasma membrane

definition.value: The component of the plasma membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes with covalently attached hyrdophobic anchors products that penetrate only the cytoplasmic side of the membrane.

label.value: TIMP family protein binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any member of the Tissue inhibitors of metalloproteinases (TIMPs) family. TIMPs are endogenous protein regulators of the matrix metalloproteinase (MMPs) family

label.value: FBXO family protein binding

definition.value: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any member of the FBXO protein family. Members of this family have an F-box protein motif of approximately 50 amino acids that functions as a site of protein-protein interaction.

label.value: phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 5 residues involved in recruitment of mRNA capping enzyme to RNA polymerase II holoenzyme complex

definition.value: Any phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 5 residues that is involved in recruitment of mRNA capping enzyme to RNA polymerase II holoenzyme complex.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter involved in determination of left|right symmetry

definition.value: Any regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter that is involved in determination of left|right symmetry.

label.value: regulation of dosage compensation by inactivation of X chromosome

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dosage compensation, by inactivation of X chromosome.

label.value: negative regulation of dosage compensation by inactivation of X chromosome

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dosage compensation, by inactivation of X chromosome.

label.value: positive regulation of dosage compensation by inactivation of X chromosome

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of dosage compensation, by inactivation of X chromosome.

label.value: regulation of nodal signaling pathway involved in determination of left|right asymmetry

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a nodal signaling pathway, where the nodal signaling pathway is involved in determination of left|right asymmetry.

label.value: negative regulation of nodal signaling pathway involved in determination of left|right asymmetry

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a nodal signaling pathway, where the nodal signaling pathway is involved in determination of left|right asymmetry.

label.value: nodal signaling pathway involved in determination of lateral mesoderm left|right asymmetry

definition.value: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a nodal protein to an activin receptor on the surface of a target cell, which contributes to the establishment of lateral mesoderm with respect to the left and right halves.

label.value: regulation of nodal signaling pathway involved in determination of lateral mesoderm left|right asymmetry

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a nodal signaling pathway, where the nodal signaling pathway is involved in determination of left|right asymmetry in the lateral mesoderm.

label.value: negative regulation of nodal signaling pathway involved in determination of lateral mesoderm left|right asymmetry

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a nodal signaling pathway, where the nodal signaling pathway is involved in determination of left|right asymmetry in the lateral mesoderm.

label.value: positive regulation of nodal signaling pathway involved in determination of lateral mesoderm left|right asymmetry

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of nodal signaling pathway involved in determination of lateral mesoderm left|right asymmetry.

label.value: regulation of cytoplasmic translational elongation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cytoplasmic translational elongation.

label.value: negative regulation of cytoplasmic translational elongation

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cytoplasmic translational elongation.

label.value: positive regulation of cytoplasmic translational elongation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cytoplasmic translational elongation.

label.value: regulation of mRNA polyadenylation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mRNA polyadenylation.

label.value: negative regulation of mRNA polyadenylation

definition.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mRNA polyadenylation.

label.value: positive regulation of mRNA polyadenylation

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mRNA polyadenylation.
